gomodel:SYNGO_5214  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 4c: SHARPIN is enriched in PSD biochemical fractions from rat brain (similar to Shank).\n\nFigure 5: reverse-IP in COS7 cells and rat cerebella showed that SHARPIN and SHANK1 can interact.\n\nFigure 6, 8: immunofluorescence imaging showed SHARPIN and SHANK1 partially co-localized at excitatory postsynapses in cultured hippocampal neurons and cerebellum tissue.. Experimental description: M&M:\n\"Immunohistochemistry on Brain Sections and Cultured Neurons - Adult rats were perfused with 4% paraformaldehyde, and brain sections (50 mm) were cut using Vibratome after overnight postfixation.\"\n\nantibody:\n\"To make Sharpin antibodies (1125, 9538, and 9716), the insert from the pGAD10 SR232 clone (aa 1-381 of Sharpin) was subcloned in frame into pRSETB (hexahistidine (H6) fusion protein vector; Invitrogen). Fusion proteins were purified by using Probond resin (Invitrogen) and used to immunize three rabbits (1125, 9538, and 9716). Sharpin-specific antibodies were purified from serum by using H6-Sharpin fusion proteins immobilized to PVDF membrane (Amersham Pharmacia Biotech). For double-immunofluorescence staining between Sharpin and Shank, we made a guinea pig Sharpin, a Novel Postsynaptic Density Protein 393 polyclonal Shank antibody (1123 and 1124) by using the GST fusion protein containing the SH3 1 PDZ domain (aa 469-691) of Shank1 as immunogen. Shank-specific antibodies were affinity-purified by using the Sulfolink column (Pierce) immobilized with thioredoxin fusion protein (pET32a; Novagen) containing the same insert as immunogen\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2023-03-03" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5214" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

